  "13-3": (
    caption: [Chemical properties of carbonyl groups. (a) The carbon atom of a carbonyl group is an electrophile by virtue of the electron- withdrawing capacity of the electronegative oxygen atom, which results in a structure in which the carbon has a partial positive charge. (b) Within a molecule, delocalization of electrons into a carbonyl group stabilizes a carbanion on an adjacent carbon, facilitating its formation. (c) Imines function much like carbonyl groups in facilitating electron withdrawal. (d) Carbonyl groups do not always function alone; their capacity as electron sinks often is augmented by interaction with either a metal ion (Me21, such as Mg21) or a general acid (HA). 13.2 Chemical Logic and Common Biochemical Reactions 513 O R2 R1 C (cid:3) C R3 C O H(cid:2) O R2 R3 R1 C C C],
